purejavahidapi

Class HidDeviceInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • purejavahidapi.HidDeviceInfo

  • public class HidDeviceInfo
extends Object
    HidDeviceInfo instances represent all that can be found out about a specific connected USB HID device without actually opening it. Basically the information that the lower level USB system learns from the device descriptor when the devise is plugged in.

    For more details of see the USB Specification.

    Author:
    nyholku

    • Method Detail

      • getPath

        public String getPath()
        This method returns a string that represents a platform dependent path that describes the 'physical' path through hubs and ports to the device.

        The main use of the path is to pass it to the PureJavaHidApi.openDevice(HidDeviceInfo) to obtain a HidDevice instance which can subsequently be used to communicate with the device.

        Returns:
        a string representing a 'path' to the device

      • getVendorId

        public short getVendorId()
        This method returns the 16 bit Vendor Id of the device.

        Note that the return type is short so when compared against literals or variables of type int sign extension interferes and thus it is necessary to cast the int type to short.

        Returns:
        the 16 bit Vendor Id
